reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for work
reviews.reviewText: These are great for work I like that they come with their own carrying case and they are not flimsy by no means they are very stout and they’re really easy to clean. Just throw them in your dishwasher and you’re good to go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The quality is good. Not heavy nor flimsy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for lunch box
reviews.reviewText: I managed to throw my old knife and fork in the trash (or that is my strong assumption) by mistake as I was cleaning my lunch container at work. Made do for a while with less than perfect substitutes but now it was time to upgrade. I didn't want to take from my silverware stash at home, nor did I want to buy a 20-piece set for this relatively simple need. I didn't spend a whole lot of time researching and decided to splurge my $6-7 on this set. The only negative comments seemed to center around the somewhat flimsy plastic container and I second those sentiments. So I immediately wrapped a rubber band around the box as it was unlikely to stay closed otherwise. Besides that I think the box is adequate and even has room for a set of chopsticks should I need those).The utensils themselves are actually quite nice: rounded & smooth edges (unlike in my previous set) and I'd be surprised to see any rust (again unlike my previous set), normal adult size with enough heft so they don't feel like they are going to bend too easily. These are perfect for my work lunch needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Utensils great, case not so much
reviews.reviewText: The utensils themselves are great. A little smaller than full size but not too small. The case, as others have mentioned, is not sturdy enough. I dropped it yesterday for the first time and a chunk immediately cracked off, leaving an opening on one end. The opening is large enough for the handles of the utensils to slide through.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice quality and functional
reviews.reviewText: Love the pouch with the loop making it easy to carry. The utensils are functional and good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Was exactly what I was looking for, a good quality regular set of one spoon, knife and fork. Very portable and doesn’t take up much space at all, I love that it has the travel case. Perfect since I had moved into a dorm and didn’t want to keep spending money on plastic ones, or have more than necessary with more dishes to do.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Silverware in a nice solid carrying case
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this silverware set for days I work in a shared workspace. Simply keep in my rolling briefcase and I'm all set. Chose stainless steel since easy to clean, nice looking and keeps those germs at bay. Must admit...the carry case is super cute. All I did was wrap the fork, knife and spoon in a couple of napkins, they fit no problem inside the case - and it's off to the shared office. Will save a ton not having to purchase plastic cutlery sets anymore. Some restaurants are cutting back on providing plastic utensils with to-go orders. Great to have my own personal set whenever I need it. Carrying case could fit in a large handbag, backpack or tote too. Doesn't take up a lot of space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Overall good for the price
reviews.reviewText: The silverware itself is really nice, it is sturdy and has a good weight behind it. The silverware is really easy to clean. My biggest problem with the product is the carrying case, which is really why I bought the kit for the case. The first time I purchased this product, the case broke within a week, it was returned and replaced. Now a little over a month later, the case broke again in the same manner. I can still use the case but the break is probably going to spread and it is very disappointing that it broke twice in the same way.

reviews.reviewTitle: Cutlery is exactly what is needed. The case will not stay closed, a rubber band needed for that job
reviews.reviewText: Is there a secret to ensuring the case keeps the cutlery inside. I will be taking it with me in my handbag, NOT a lunch box/bag.
